<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 27 at 3:39PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Band of Snowfall Reducing Visibility Across Central Montana...
A band of snow is overspread much of Central Montana as of 330 PM,
moving slowly southward. This band of snow may briefly reduce
visibility to a half mile or less for a brief period. The
combination of gusty winds and snow is likely to make travel
difficult. Expect driving conditions to change suddenly near the
band of snow. Overall, snow associated with this band will last
generally an hour or less.</description>
